            </div>

            <div class="callout">

                <p>You can also install VPN and proxy extensions in the browser you use. This is very simple. First, you need to find an extension (or add-on) shop via any search engine. Then type "VPN" or "proxy" into the search box and install the extension. You may have to try several options. On the page of the extension you've chosen, there will be instructions on how to use it. But more often than not, it's just a matter of clicking on its icon at the top right and clicking the enable button. In some cases, you can select the country you're supposed to be logging in from.
                </p>
                <p>VPNs and proxies operate differently. In the first case, a virtual private network is created, thereby masking you, while in the second, you are physically connected to a computer that is in another country. In both cases, there is nothing the ISP can do about it, as it cannot block the private network or the computer in the other country. You can use this method even if you are having problems right now and have not previously taken care of <a href="../mirrorsite" title="mirror 1xbet">mirrors</a> or 1xBrowser.
